  "correction_2026_06_26": "An earlier release reported 412 findings (ℕ 27 / ℝ 320 / ℝ-with-hyp 16) and a 2% with-hypothesis control. A bug in the candidate filter extracted identifiers from concatenated relation sides without a separator, forging phantom variables (e.g. 'n'+'n - 1' -> 'nn') and silently rejecting valid candidates — FALSE NEGATIVES ONLY, so no prior finding was invalid; the counts were undercounts. Fixed; corrected to 534 total (ℕ 31 / ℝ 335 / ℝ-with-hyp 119), control 24% vs 5.4%. Every finding kernel-confirmed (native_decide ℕ, norm_num ℝ)."
